REM Clears the screen
CLS

REM Collect key story elements from the player
ECHO.
ECHO.
ECHO.
ECHO.

REM Collect the name of Buzz's owner
SET /p player=1. What is your name? 

ECHO.

REM Collect the name of the wonder dog
SET /p wonderdog=2. Give your dog a name: 

ECHO.

REM Collect the name of player's hangout
SET /p hangout=3. Where is your favorite place to hang out? 

ECHO.

REM Collect the piece of clothing Buzz grabs to save owner
SET /p clothes=4. Name of a piece of clothing: 

ECHO.

REM Collect vehicle that almost runs over Buzz's owner
SET /p vehicle=5. Name a type of 4-wheel motor vehicle: 

ECHO.

REM Collect body part Buzz grabs to save owner
SET /p bodypart=6. Name a part of the human body: 

ECHO.

REM Collect what type of animal almost runs over Buzz's owner
SET /p animal=7. What is your favorite animal? 

ECHO.
ECHO.
ECHO These look like really good answers. Now, let's get on with the story.
ECHO.
ECHO.
ECHO.

REM Waits for player to push any key
PAUSE

REM Clears the screen
CLS

REM Displays story with player input
ECHO.
ECHO.
ECHO.
ECHO.
ECHO.
ECHO.
ECHO Once upon a time, there lived a very special little dog called %wonderdog%.
ECHO.
ECHO %wonderdog%'s best friend was his owner, %player%. %wonderdog% and %player% went everywhere
ECHO.
ECHO together. Sunday was their favorite day to spend together because on
ECHO.
ECHO that day they would play down by the %hangout%.
ECHO.
ECHO.
ECHO.
ECHO.
ECHO.
ECHO.
ECHO.
ECHO.
ECHO.
ECHO.

REM Waits for player to push any key
